events.name: Study Jams - UET Peshawar
events.description:
Many people learn better when they learn in groups. Web Study Jams is a GDG Islamabad community-run study group for developers covering mobile web design and development. This current study jam will be about Mobile Site Certification. The Study Jams objective is to raise the technical proficiency of global community members through the highest possible course completion rate.

Mobile Site Certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate understanding in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

How long does it take: Approximately 3-4 hours of study material, followed by 90 minute (multiple choice) exam

End Result: Students that complete the exam receive a printable certificate to verify status as a certified mobile sites professional and a Google Partners public profile page listing the certification.

events.name: Flutter Study Jam
events.description:
Google Developers Group Islamabad, in collaboration with DEMO Entreprise and Coders Stack will execute it`s very first Flutter Study Jams. The aim is to spread awareness among local developer about Flutter and it`s practical implementations. The workshop will be comprised of three workshop sessions (hands-on training) as per Google Study Jam guide. At the end of the workshop, the participant will demonstrate their Demo Apps (build during three days) before a certificate celebration.

Instructor:
Muhammad Zeeshan Khan, Co-Founder AptechMedia Solutions is a passionate developer having 4 years+ experience as a full-stack web developer. Mr. Zeeshan is also fond of exploring and learning new technologies, he had also explored Flutter and build 3+ applications based on Flutter.

Agenda:
2:00 pm: Flutter Udacity Course Introduction
2:10 pm: Udacity Course Lesson 1
3:30 pm: Break
4:00 pm: Udacity Course Lesson 1 continue
5:00 pm: Event ends
*same agenda for Lesson 2 and Lesson 3

Date:
10 - 12 October 2018
2 - 5 PM (PST)

Participants:
15 - 20 (beginner and intermediate level) programmers.

Eligibility:
Must have programming basics.
Must know Object Oriented Programming
Must understand the concept of classes, structure, stack and heap etc.

Tool:
Participant must have Android Studio install in their laptops (hands-on training).

Venue:
National Incubation Center, Peshawar

events.name: DevFest 2018
events.description:
GDG DevFest 2018 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, workshops, tech talks and more!

Join us on the 17th November for a day filled with enlightening discussions and workshops around Google technologies such as Android, Firebase, Google Cloud Platform, Google Assistant, Flutter, machine learning with TensorFlow, and Mobile Web.

Our theme this year is "Digital WellBeing" where we will highlight and discuss the tools and features that help people better understand their tech usage, focus on what matters most, disconnect when needed, and create healthy habits so that LIFE, not the technology in it, stays front and center.

Follow our event on Facebook for regular updates and additional information https://www.facebook.com/events/166190560953152/

events.name: Cloud Study Jam 2019 - Peshawar
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, applications deployment.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want

For more details of the event and registration visit: https://www.facebook.com/events/414998255709842/

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam 2019 - COMSATS Islamabad
events.description:
Study Jams are community-run study groups for developers. This is a great opportunity to bring members of the community together to learn something in person. These training will give the community members a specific skill they can use for personal development or career advancement.

With a Cloud Study Jam, you will learn the fundamental tools and capabilities of Google Cloud. Attendees will receive free access to our online labs. You can choose any of our recommended tracks to run with the community: Machine Learning, Kubernetes, Certification, IoT, and Security.

After the session, attendees can continue taking labs to earn Google Cloud badges.

==============================================

Cloud Study Jams 2019 Islamabad Topics:
►Introduction to Qwiklabs
►Setting up virtual machine or window environment
►Intro to cloud shell and google cloud
►Hello node kubernetes
►Stack driver: Qwikstart
►Setting up network and HTTP Loaders
►Provision services with GCP marketplace
►Creating a persistent disk
Note:
No eligibility criterion is required.Anyone willing to learn more about the topics mentioned above ca join the session.

Timing: 11:30 am - 1:30 pm | 2 hours
Venue: COMSATS Islamabad

events.name: Google Developer Student Club Awareness Session

venue.name: National University of Sciences and Technology (NUST)

events.description:
GDG Islamabad in partnership with SEECS Alumni Association is arranging an awareness session regarding a recently launched program of Google in Pakistan, Developer Student Clubs.

DSC help thousands of student developers learn and work with their communities to solve real-life problems. Join us to learn more about this program from Saad Hamid who is currently the Developer Community Manager at Google.

We encourage freshmen, sophomores, and juniors to attend this interactive session.

events.name: WTMIslamabad Webinar: Google's Women Techmakers Scholars Program
events.description:
If you are a female student pursuing CS or other tech-related majors and aren't graduating before 2020, then here is an exciting opportunity for you.

Google Women Techmakers Scholarship application is open these days (http://womentechmakers.com/scholars)

GDG Islamabad in partnership with Pakistani Women In Computing - PWiC is organising an informative and interactive session so that you can learn from the past WTM Scholars about the program and how to maximize your chances of getting accepted.

More information about the program here: http://bit.ly/WTMScholarProgram

NOTE: A meeting link with be provided after the registration.
